t">ts without lights must be punished, it’s not fair on anyone who is involved in accident with an unlit cyclist, there’s no excuse for it.  A zero tolerance approach should be adopted to cyclists who aren’t visible to drivers. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Police and learner drivers sh</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">ould undergo cycle awareness training. New drivers so that they understand the challenges facing a cyclist and will be able to predict movements (dodging a drain cover etc) and not got lost up their own asses with self importance when a cyclist slows them </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">down by a couple of seconds. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Police need to understand why cyclists do what they do at traffic lights and not issue fines in a black and white manner. If it is obvious that a cyclist has moved infront of the white line to protect themselves there should b</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">e no fine. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">December 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>